1. *Licem* prema suncu se nije dobro okrenuti. (Facing *towards* the sun is not good.)
2. Njihova *lica* su bila prekrivena maskama. (Their *faces* were covered with masks.)
3. Učiteljica se *licem* obraćala deci. (The teacher addressed the children *face-to-face*.)
4. Ona je svojim *licem* pokazala svoje nezadovoljstvo. (She showed her displeasure *with her face*.)
5. *Licem* u lice suočio se sa svojim strahom. (He faced his fear *head-on*.)
6. Kada je čula vest, *licem* joj se odrazio šok. (When she heard the news, *her face* reflected shock.)
7. On je bio osoba koju je teško pročitati po *licu*. (He was a person who was hard to read *by his face*.)
8. Zgrada je okrenuta *licem* prema moru. (The building is facing *towards* the sea.)
9. Bila je ljuta, *lice* joj je bilo crveno. (She was angry, *her face* was red.)
10. Da bismo se bolje upoznali, treba da se upoznamo *licem* u lice. (To get to know each other better, we need to meet *face-to-face*.)